# Splunk Process Tree Detection Lab — Parent and Child Process Investigation

## Overview

This lab focuses on process creation monitoring and process tree analysis using Splunk and Windows Security Event Logs.

The objective of the lab was to understand how parent-child process relationships appear in Windows telemetry and how SOC analysts reconstruct execution chains during investigations.

Using Windows Event ID 4688, I investigated:

* Process creation events
* Parent-child process relationships
* PowerShell execution chains
* Hidden PowerShell execution
* Suspicious process spawning behavior

This lab was performed using a Windows virtual machine forwarding logs into Splunk Enterprise hosted on Ubuntu.

